+# Hermes Acceptance Semantic Coverage and Rich Checks Plan
+
+> For Hermes: Use subagent-driven-development skill to implement this plan task-by-task.
+
+Date: 2026-04-21
+Repo: `~/.hermes/hermes-agent`
+
+Goal: Strengthen Hermes acceptance beyond improved contract inference by making per-criterion acceptance less dependent on shallow wording overlap and by expanding the executable-check library for concrete artifacts and outputs.
+
+Architecture: Keep the current acceptance architecture intact (`TaskContract` -> `VerificationCheck` -> `CheckResult` -> `AcceptanceResult` -> parent finalizer), and focus the next phase on two layers: (1) stronger criterion/result binding and normalization in `agent/acceptance.py`, and (2) a broader but still deterministic set of executable checks that provide better evidence for artifact-oriented tasks. Preserve the current parent-finalizer and persistence interfaces so existing CLI/gateway status surfaces continue to work without schema churn.
+
+Tech Stack: Python, regex/string normalization heuristics, deterministic local checks in `agent/acceptance.py`, pytest via `uv run --extra dev pytest`.
+
+---
+
+## Current Baseline
+
+Verified from the current repo state:
+
+- Contract inference upgrades are already implemented and tested.
+- `tests/agent/test_acceptance.py` currently passes with 39 tests.
+- Targeted parent-finalizer regressions currently pass (7 tests).
+- Current acceptance still has two important limitations:
+  1. criterion satisfaction is largely lexical/structural
+  2. executable checks are still a narrow library
+
+Current executable checks include:
+- `command`
+- `file_exists`
+- `file_contains`
+- `file_not_contains`
+- `stdout_regex`
+- `stdout_not_regex`
+- `json_field_match`
+
+## Problem Statement
+
+Even with stronger contract inference, acceptance can still be weak in two ways:
+
+1. A criterion may be truly satisfied but marked inconclusive because transcript wording differs from the criterion text.
+2. A task may have a concrete deliverable shape that current executable checks cannot express cleanly.
+
+This phase should therefore improve:
+- semantic-ish criterion coverage without introducing an LLM judge
+- richer deterministic checks for concrete deliverables
+
+## Success Criteria
+
+1. Criterion matching becomes more robust to wording variants via stronger normalization/token handling.
+2. Explicit criterion-bound executable evidence outranks shallow transcript mismatch when appropriate.
+3. New deterministic check kinds expand acceptance coverage for common artifact/result tasks.
+4. Existing parent-finalizer behavior remains compatible.
+5. New behavior is introduced test-first and verified with narrow + regression pytest runs.
+
+## Constraints
+
+- No LLM-as-judge pass in this phase.
+- Keep checks deterministic and locally executable.
+- Avoid changing the persisted acceptance-report schema unless strictly necessary.
+- Preserve current `AcceptanceResult` and parent-finalizer integration.
+- Prefer a small number of high-value new check kinds over speculative generality.
+
+## Non-Goals
+
+- No CLI/gateway UX redesign in this phase.
+- No strict-mode policy redesign in this phase.
+- No background evaluator or async acceptance worker.
+
+## Main Risks
+
+1. Criterion normalization may become too permissive and create false passes.
+2. New check kinds may overlap awkwardly with current checks and create noisy acceptance results.
+3. Regression surface may widen if helper behavior is changed too broadly.
+
+## Verification Strategy
+
+- Add failing tests for each new criterion-matching behavior and each new check kind.
+- Run targeted tests first.
+- Re-run full `tests/agent/test_acceptance.py` after each cluster of changes.
+- Re-run the current targeted parent-finalizer regression slice before closing.
+
+---
+
+## File Plan
+
+### Modified files
+- Modify: `agent/acceptance.py`
+- Modify: `tests/agent/test_acceptance.py`
+
+### Reference files
+- Reference: `docs/acceptance-framework-design.md`
+- Reference: `tests/run_agent/test_run_agent.py`
+
+---
+
+## Task 1: Strengthen criterion normalization and coverage tests
+
+**Objective:** Reduce false inconclusive results caused by wording variants.
+
+**Files:**
+- Modify: `tests/agent/test_acceptance.py`
+- Modify: `agent/acceptance.py`
+
+**Step 1: Write a failing test for criterion/pass with wording variation**
+
+Example:
+
+```python
+def test_evaluate_claim_evidence_consistency_accepts_semantically_close_provider_label_wording():
+    contract = TaskContract(
+        task_summary="fix provider label",
+        deliverable="provider label fixed",
+        success_criteria=["show named custom provider in the status bar"],
+        verification_checks=[VerificationCheck(id="transcript_coverage", description="...", kind="transcript_coverage")],
+    )
+    messages = [{"role": "assistant", "content": "The status bar now shows the selected custom provider name."}]
+
+    result = evaluate_claim_evidence_consistency(contract, messages)
+
+    assert result.status == "pass"
+```
+
+**Step 2: Run the narrow test to verify RED**
